<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: TEMPLE CITY; 
</P>
<P>
FREE DIAL-A-RIDE TRIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Residents will again be able to use the city's Dial-a-Ride program for free 
this Christmas season. 
</P>
<P>
The 50-cent one-way fare for the program, under which residents can call for 
door-to-door van service to locations around the city, was waived last December 
to encourage ridership during the holiday season. 
</P>
<P>
The free service proved so popular that the City Council decided Tuesday to 
offer it again this year. The fee waiver is allowed under Los Angeles County 
Transportation Commission guidelines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
