<HEADLINE>
<P>
RACING AT BAY MEADOWS IS POSTPONED UNTIL STRUCTURAL DAMAGE CAN BE DETERMINED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thoroughbred racing at Bay Meadows was postponed Wednesday and today until 
engineers at the track on the San Francisco Peninsula can determine the amount 
of structural damage caused by Tuesday's earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
Bay Meadows, which is located in San Mateo, a few miles south of San Francisco 
International Airport, doesn't race on Tuesdays. Structural damage to the 
track's grandstand is believed to be minor, a spokesman at the track said. BILL 
CHRISTINE 
</P>
</TEXT>
