<P>
BOEING STRIKE TALKS LAST ONLY 3 1/2 HOURS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Talks aimed at ending a 2-week-old walkout by 57,800 Boeing Co. machinists 
ended after just 3 1/2 hours and federal mediator Doug Hammond said he did not 
know when negotiations would resume. The two sides were kept in separate rooms 
at Hammond's Seattle office so any suggestions of changes in the contract would 
be kept unofficial. When meeting face-to-face the suggested changes become 
official positions. There are concerns within the aircraft giant and among 
customers about delays in aircraft deliveries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
