<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 4 ARRESTED IN EXTORTION; ASIAN GANG TIES 
ALLEGED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four men thought to be members of an Asian organized crime network, the United 
Bamboo Gang, were arrested Wednesday on suspicion of trying to extort $200,000 
from a Paramount businessman, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The arrests came after sheriff's deputies used search warrants to enter five 
San Gabriel Valley locations, Deputy Dean Scoville said. 
</P>
<P>
At four residences and one nightclub, deputies seized handguns, assault rifles 
and one "Street Sweeper" semiautomatic shotgun. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies and Los Angeles and Monterey Park police began investigating 
reports of attempted extortion about a week ago, Scoville said. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies did not release the name of the victim or how he was being extorted. 
</P>
<P>
The four men arrested were identified as Khu Ca Ha, 47, of Rosemead; Hsiu Chun 
Huang, 35, of Hacienda Heights; Huy Cham Tran, 24, of Houston, and Billy Chi 
Kang Yang, 40, of Alhambra. 
</P>
</TEXT>
