BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MGM Files Lawsuit Against Qintex: MGM/UA Communications has filed a $20-million 
lawsuit against the domestic arm of its former suitor, claiming Qintex America 
Ltd. has not made $3 million worth of payments for a TV development deal. The 
complaint filed in U.S. District Court in Los Angeles claims that Qintex has 
neglected to make payments for August, September and October. MGM/UA claims 
Qintex agreed in April, 1988, to a co-financing venture involving American 
network television programming. The contract is guaranteed by Qintex's parent, 
Qintex Australia Ltd. 
</P>
