<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
PANELISTS TO DEVELOP CHILD-CARE STRATEGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Representatives of community organizations and local businesses will be getting 
together in the next few months to talk about ways that child-care services can 
be improved in the city. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council voted this week to hire a consultant to coordinate a "child 
care consortium" charged with developing a child-care strategy for Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
The consultant, National Pediatric Support Services Inc., will organize 
consortium meetings, develop an informational booklet on child-care options, 
help employers with child-care assessments and write the consortium's 
child-care plan. 
</P>
<P>
The plan is scheduled to be completed in about four months. A $20,600 grant 
from the state Department of Education is paying for the program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
