<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 CAMP PENDLETON BRUSH FIRES BURN, ONE IN CLEVELAND FOREST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two brush fires blackened at least 250 acres of Camp Pendleton Wednesday, a 
Marine Corps spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The first fire was reported at 11:15 a.m. in San Mateo Canyon just south of 
Orange County and burned 200 acres in the northern part of the base and a 
portion of the Cleveland National Forest, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The second fire broke out at about 4:30 p.m. and had burned about 50 acres near 
the Camp Horno area of Camp Pendleton close to San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured in either blaze, and officials don't know how the fires were 
started. A Marine Coprs spokesman said late Wednesday night that firefighters 
were still battling both blazes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
