<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRUG NAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I love it! Finally an honest name for a drug -- Croak ("Potent Form of Speed 
Could Be Drug of '90s," Oct. 8). I lost a lot of friends many years ago through 
drug use. I used to wonder why people give drugs cutesy names, like Blue Cheer 
and Orange Sunshine for LSD. And what's so cheerful about being in the psych 
ward at Metropolitan State Mental Hospital? Sunshine is something you don't see 
much of behind bars. 
</P>
<P>
Let's dump these cute names. 
</P>
<P>
FRED J. HERMON 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
