<HEADLINE>
<P>
SATURDAY'S HEROES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Following are last week's top collegiate football performances by South Bay 
high school graduates: 
</P>
<P>
 Leroy Hall, USC, senior: The former Banning fullback rushed for a career-high 
160 yards on 21 carries and scored on a 55-yard run in a 31-15 win over UC 
Berkeley. 
</P>
<P>
Dan Speltz, Cal State Fullerton, senior: The former Rolling Hills quarterback 
completed 17 of 22 passes for 228 yards and one touchdown in a 35-26 victory 
over Pacific. He ranks fourth in the nation in passing, averaging 152.5 yards a 
game. 
</P>
<P>
Ken Sale, Texas-El Paso, senior: The former Bishop Montgomery linebacker has a 
team-high 11 tackles in 26-7 win over New Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
Dominic Cefalone, Texas-El Paso, junior: The former West Torrance kicker had 
field goals of 45, 30 and 35 yards in the Miner's win. 
</P>
<P>
Errol Sapp, Arizona, freshman: The former Carson running back gained 77 yards 
on 12 carries and scored the Wildcats' final touchdown on a 14-yard run in a 
42-7 win over UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
Brian Treggs, UC Berkeley, sophomore: The former Carson wide receiver caught 
three passes for 129 yards, including touchdowns of 75 and 14 yards, in a loss 
to USC. 
</P>
<P>
Pee Wee Smith, Miami, senior: The former Gardena wide receiver had a 63-yard 
punt return in a 48-16 win over San Jose State. 
</P>
</TEXT>
