</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An overwhelming 99% of BAT Industries PLC's shareholders today approved a major 
defensive restructuring planned by the British conglomerate, including the sale 
of all its U.S. retailing operations. 
</P>
<P>
BAT's plan is aimed at increasing shareholder value in an attempt to thwart a 
hostile all-paper $21-billion bid from an investor group led by Sir James 
Goldsmith. 
</P>
<P>
The purchase would be the world's second largest takeover after the $25-billion 
acquisition of RJR Nabisco Inc. completed earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
BAT is the world's biggest tobacco company and has substantial operations in 
retailing -- including the Saks Fifth Avenue and Marshall Field chains in the 
United States -- paper and financial services. 
