<P>
OLDER MANAGERS FIND JOBS FASTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Out-of-work managers over age 50 found jobs faster than their younger 
colleagues in the job market last summer, according to a survey released today 
by Challenger, Gray &amp; Christmas Inc. 
</P>
<P>
"The results represent the first time in 15 years of tracking job searches that 
the 50-and-over age group has surpassed its younger counterparts in the length 
of time it takes to find a new job," said James E. Challenger, president and 
founder of the job-search consulting firm. 
</P>
<P>
The firm's survey of third-quarter employment patterns showed the median time 
needed for an out-of-work manager age 50 or over to find new work was 3.23 
months. Unemployed managers in all other age groups required a median time of 
3.26 months. 
</P>
