<P>
SHOEMAKER WINS 1 DOWN UNDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MELBOURNE, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
l Shoemaker, who has won more than 8,800 horse races worldwide, scored his 
first triumph in Australia today. 
</P>
<P>
His victory Down Under came in the Moe Cup, a race held annually in a small 
Australian bush town. Shoemaker, visiting for the first time as part of a 
farewell tour, rode 8-1 shot Cosign to victory, which offered total prize money 
of only $40,000. 
</P>
<P>
Shoemaker's visit captivated the small coal mining town of Moe, west of 
Melbourne. 
</P>
<P>
"This has made my visit to Australia one of my best moments in racing," 
Shoemaker, 58, said after riding Cosign to a 1 3/4-lengths win over Ima Red 
Man. 
</P>
<P>
"I've been going to come to Australia many times over the past 20 years only to 
be disappointed through home commitments, and I did not want to go back to 
America without a winner," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
